{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0e7ef996-fbf9-4496-b88d-dd0e8f5ae4a3","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory. Could you share the path to your dump file?\n\nIn the meantime, here's how to analyze it:\n\n### Recommended Tool: `dotnet-dump`\n\n1. **Install it:**\n   ```\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   ```\n\n2. **Analyze the dump:**\n   ```\n   dotnet-dump analyze /path/to/your.dmp\n   ```\n\n3. **Useful SOS commands inside the analyzer:**\n   | Command | Purpose |\n   |---|---|\n   | `clrstack` | Managed call stack of the crashing thread |\n   | `pe` (PrintException) | Last exception details + stack trace |\n   | `dumpheap -stat` | Heap overview (OOM investigations) |\n   | `threads` | List all managed threads |\n   | `clrstack -all` | Stacks for all threads |\n   | `dso` (DumpStackObjects) | Objects on the current thread's stack |\n\n### Quick workflow\n```\n> dotnet-dump analyze crash.dmp\n> pe           # see the exception\n> clrstack     # see where it crashed\n> threads      # check all threads\n```\n\nIf you can upload or point me to the dump file, I can walk through the analysis with you. Otherwise, would you like help installing `dotnet-dump` and getting started?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"74d3ed73-7c60-451f-b334-ebbed87b088e","outputTokens":329,"requestId":"2C43:1EA0BA:150983B:17DDE0C:69F94EE4"},"id":"b809a80a-0061-4cdd-9151-da2715829221","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:59:09.568Z","parentId":"12d793d3-9bb5-47c1-a720-e539f3f59351"}
